"'''Sour Candy'''" is a song by Canadian singer/songwriter [[Carly Rae Jepsen]], released in October 2009 as the fourth and final single from her debut studio album, ''[[Tug of War (Carly Rae Jepsen album)|Tug of War]]''. The song was written by Jepsen and [[Marianas Trench (band)|Marianas Trench]] lead vocalist [[Josh Ramsay]], who also produced the song and is featured as a vocalist on the single version.<ref>{{cite news|title=Carly Rae Jepsen on CBC Music|url=http://music.cbc.ca/#!/artists/Carly-Rae-Jepsen|accessdate=11 March 2015|work=[[CBC Music]]|publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Carly Rae Jepsen|url=http://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.ca/en/article/carly-rae-jepsen/|publisher=[[The Canadian Encyclopedia]]|accessdate=11 March 2015}}</ref> It failed to chart on the [[Canadian Hot 100]], but did enter the [[Canada Hot AC]] airplay chart monitored by [[Nielsen Broadcast Data Systems|''Nielsen'' BDS Radio]].<ref name=hot-AC/>

==Content==
This song discusses the loss of a relationship, which Jepsen refers to as a "sour candy ending."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://artists.letssingit.com/carly-rae-jepsen-lyrics-sour-candy-4xmx9rs|title=Carly Rae Jepsen - Sour Candy Lyrics|accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref> The main instrument used is acoustic guitar.

==Music video==
The music video for "Sour Candy" was shot in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia|BC]] and directed by Ben Knechtel.<ref name=video-vimeo>{{cite web|last1=Knechtel|first1=Ben|title=Carly Rae Jepsen "Sour Candy" Music Video on Vimeo|url=https://vimeo.com/8215131|publisher=[[Vimeo]]|accessdate=11 March 2015|date=16 December 2009}}</ref> It premiered 16 December 2009 and was uploaded to Jepsen's [[Vevo]] channel on 5 July 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=egA-UEDoN_M|title=Carly Rae Jepsen - Sour Candy ft. Josh Ramsay|author=CarlyRaeJepsenVEVO|work=[[YouTube]]|publisher=[[Google]]|accessdate=27 April 2014|date=5 July 2011}}</ref> It tells the story of two estranged lovers (played by Jepsen and Ramsay) in couple's therapy.<ref name=video-vimeo/>

